10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to veterans; imposing requirements on
executive governmental entities to provide
12 information related to certain donations; providing
for apportionment or deposit of amounts donated;
13 requiring government websites to provide information
related to certain donations; providing for
14 codification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
15
16
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 7201 of Title 74, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. Each state agency, board, commission, department, or other
24 entity organized within the executive department shall include on
HB3078 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 any of its forms as described by subsection B of this section a link
2 to the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs or similar method in
3 order to allow a person making payment to such governmental entity
4 to make a donation to the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs
5 Revolving Fund.
6 B. The provisions of this section shall include, but shall not
7 be limited to:
8 1. Driver license applications;
9 2. Motor vehicle registrations and renewals;
10 3. Fishing and hunting license applications;
11 4. Income tax forms; and
12 5. Any other transaction during which an executive agency
13 issues a license or utilizes a form that could contain the
14 information prescribed by subsection A of this section.
15 C. If payment for any item or service described in this section
16 can be made through a website owned or maintained on behalf of the
17 governmental entity, the website shall have a conspicuous area which
18 clearly indicates that the payor may utilize the website to make a
19 donation to the Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs Revolving
20 Fund.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
22 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
24
